{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887452120,"sessionID":"ses_284dc67edffeQA8vXFiu99qzyB","part":{"id":"prt_d7b240382001DAaoO52cLy2zPC","messageID":"msg_d7b23f24a001Z3WqjV9IGZ4K3r","sessionID":"ses_284dc67edffeQA8vXFiu99qzyB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c51d5d9200c84867bcf8aeac","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/cli.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/cli.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: cli\n3: title: CLI Reference\n4: description: Command-line interface reference\n5: sidebar_position: 3\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # CLI Reference\n9: \n10: AgentCube provides a command-line interface for managing agents and deployments.\n11: \n12: ## Installation\n13: \n14: ### macOS\n15: \n16: ```bash\n17: brew install agentcube-cli\n18: ```\n19: \n20: ### Linux\n21: \n22: ```bash\n23: curl -L https://agentcube.io/install.sh | sh\n24: ```\n25: \n26: ### From Source\n27: \n28: ```bash\n29: git clone https://github.com/agentcube/agentcube.git\n30: cd agentcube\n31: go install ./cmd/cli\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ## Commands\n35: \n36: ### init\n37: \n38: Initialize a new AgentCube project.\n39: \n40: ```bash\n41: agentcube init [project-name]\n42: ```\n43: \n44: **Options:**\n45: \n46: | Flag | Description |\n47: |------|-------------|\n48: | `--template` | Project template (default, api, webhook) |\n49: | `--force` | Overwrite existing files |\n50: \n51: **Example:**\n52: \n53: ```bash\n54: agentcube init my-agent --template api\n55: ```\n56: \n57: ### login\n58: \n59: Authenticate with AgentCube.\n60: \n61: ```bash\n62: agentcube login [flags]\n63: ```\n64: \n65: **Options:**\n66: \n67: | Flag | Description |\n68: |------|-------------|\n69: | `--api-key` | API key |\n70: | `--server` | Server URL (default: https://agentcube.io) |\n71: \n72: **Example:**\n73: \n74: ```bash\n75: agentcube login --api-key YOUR_API_KEY\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### agent\n79: \n80: Manage agents.\n81: \n82: #### Create Agent\n83: \n84: ```bash\n85: agentcube agent create [flags]\n86: ```\n87: \n88: **Flags:**\n89: \n90: | Flag | Short | Description |\n91: |------|-------|-------------|\n92: | `--name` | `-n` | Agent name |\n93: | `--model` | `-m` | AI model |\n94: | `--instructions` | `-i` | Agent instructions |\n95: | `--file` | `-f` | Load from YAML file |\n96: \n97: **Example:**\n98: \n99: ```bash\n100: agentcube agent create -n my-agent -m gpt-4 -i \"You are helpful\"\n101: ```\n102: \n103: #### List Agents\n104: \n105: ```bash\n106: agentcube agent list [flags]\n107: ```\n108: \n109: **Flags:**\n110: \n111: | Flag | Description |\n112: |------|-------------|\n113: | `--status` | Filter by status |\n114: | `--output` | Output format (table, json, yaml) |\n115: \n116: **Example:**\n117: \n118: ```bash\n119: agentcube agent list --status active --output json\n120: ```\n121: \n122: #### Get Agent\n123: \n124: ```bash\n125: agentcube agent get <agent-id>\n126: ```\n127: \n128: #### Update Agent\n129: \n130: ```bash\n131: agentcube agent update <agent-id> [flags]\n132: ```\n133: \n134: #### Delete Agent\n135: \n136: ```bash\n137: agentcube agent delete <agent-id> [flags]\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Flags:**\n141: \n142: | Flag | Description |\n143: |------|-------------|\n144: | `--force` | Skip confirmation |\n145: \n146: ### invoke\n147: \n148: Invoke an agent.\n149: \n150: ```bash\n151: agentcube invoke <agent-id> [message] [flags]\n152: ```\n153: \n154: **Flags:**\n155: \n156: | Flag | Short | Description |\n157: |------|-------|-------------|\n158: | `--session` | `-s` | Session ID |\n159: | `--stream` | | Enable streaming |\n160: | `--file` | `-f` | Input from file |\n161: \n162: **Example:**\n163: \n164: ```bash\n165: agentcube invoke agent_abc123 \"Hello!\" --stream\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### runtime\n169: \n170: Manage runtimes.\n171: \n172: ```bash\n173: agentcube runtime [command]\n174: ```\n175: \n176: #### Start Runtime\n177: \n178: ```bash\n179: agentcube runtime start [flags]\n180: ```\n181: \n182: **Flags:**\n183: \n184: | Flag | Description |\n185: |------|-------------|\n186: | `--config` | Config file path |\n187: | `--port` | Port number |\n188: \n189: #### Stop Runtime\n190: \n191: ```bash\n192: agentcube runtime stop <runtime-id>\n193: ```\n194: \n195: #### List Runtimes\n196: \n197: ```bash\n198: agentcube runtime list\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ### deploy\n202: \n203: Deploy an agent to production.\n204: \n205: ```bash\n206: agentcube deploy <agent-id> [flags]\n207: ```\n208: \n209: **Flags:**\n210: \n211: | Flag | Short | Description |\n212: |------|-------|-------------|\n213: | `--env` | `-e` | Environment variables |\n214: | `--replicas` | `-r` | Number of replicas |\n215: | `--timeout` | `-t` | Deployment timeout |\n216: \n217: **Example:**\n218: \n219: ```bash\n220: agentcube deploy agent_abc123 --replicas 3 --env API_KEY=xxx\n221: ```\n222: \n223: ### logs\n224: \n225: View logs.\n226: \n227: ```bash\n228: agentcube logs <resource> [flags]\n229: ```\n230: \n231: **Flags:**\n232: \n233: | Flag | Short | Description |\n234: |------|-------|-------------|\n235: | `--follow` | `-f` | Follow logs |\n236: | `--tail` | `-t` | Number of lines |\n237: | `--since` | | Since timestamp |\n238: \n239: **Example:**\n240: \n241: ```bash\n242: agentcube logs agent_abc123 --follow --tail 100\n243: ```\n244: \n245: ### status\n246: \n247: Check status of resources.\n248: \n249: ```bash\n250: agentcube status [resource]\n251: ```\n252: \n253: **Example:**\n254: \n255: ```bash\n256: agentcube status\n257: agentcube status agent_abc123\n258: ```\n259: \n260: ### config\n261: \n262: Manage configuration.\n263: \n264: #### View Config\n265: \n266: ```bash\n267: agentcube config view\n268: ```\n269: \n270: #### Edit Config\n271: \n272: ```bash\n273: agentcube config edit\n274: ```\n275: \n276: ### version\n277: \n278: Show version information.\n279: \n280: ```bash\n281: agentcube version\n282: ```\n283: \n284: ## Configuration\n285: \n286: ### Config File\n287: \n288: AgentCube uses `agentcube.yaml` for configuration:\n289: \n290: ```yaml\n291: server: https://agentcube.io\n292: api_key: YOUR_API_KEY\n293: \n294: defaults:\n295:   model: gpt-4\n296:   timeout: 30s\n297: \n298: runtime:\n299:   port: 8080\n300:   sandbox:\n301:     enabled: true\n302: ```\n303: \n304: ### Environment Variables\n305: \n306: | Variable | Description |\n307: |----------|-------------|\n308: | `AGENTCUBE_API_KEY` | API key |\n309: | `AGENTCUBE_SERVER` | Server URL |\n310: | `AGENTCUBE_CONFIG` | Config file path |\n311: \n312: ## Completions\n313: \n314: Generate shell completions:\n315: \n316: ```bash\n317: # Bash\n318: agentcube completion bash\n319: \n320: # Zsh\n321: agentcube completion zsh\n322: \n323: # Fish\n324: agentcube completion fish\n325: ```\n326: \n327: ## Debug Mode\n328: \n329: Enable debug logging:\n330: \n331: ```bash\n332: agentcube --debug [command]\n333: ```\n334: \n335: ## Offline Mode\n336: \n337: Use AgentCube without internet:\n338: \n339: ```bash\n340: agentcube --offline [command]\n341: ```\n342: \n343: ## Troubleshooting\n344: \n345: ### Login Issues\n346: \n347: ```bash\n348: # Re-authenticate\n349: agentcube logout\n350: agentcube login --api-key YOUR_KEY\n351: ```\n352: \n353: ### Connection Issues\n354: \n355: ```bash\n356: # Check server status\n357: agentcube status\n358: \n359: # Test connectivity\n360: agentcube doctor\n361: ```\n362: \n363: ### Clear Cache\n364: \n365: ```bash\n366: agentcube cache clean\n367: ```\n368: \n369: ## Next Steps\n370: \n371: - [Agent Runtime API](/docs/api/agent-runtime)\n372: - [Code Interpreter API](/docs/api/code-interpreter)\n\n(End of file - total 372 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: cli\ntitle: CLI Reference\ndescription: Command-line interface reference\nsidebar_position: 3\n---\n\n# CLI Reference\n\nAgentCube provides a command-line interface for managing agents and deployments.\n\n## Installation\n\n### macOS\n\n```bash\nbrew install agentcube-cli\n```\n\n### Linux","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/cli.md","time":{"start":1775887452102,"end":1775887452117}}}}
